<dl id="n40055c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40055c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40055c"> 55(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> done to death / familiar</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Another way in which a demon is held to cause disease is by introducing itself into the patient&apos;s body and sucking his blood; the Malays believe that a woman who dies in childbirth becomes a langsuir and sucks the blood of children; victims of the lycanthrope are sometimes said to be done to death in the same way; and it is commonly believed in Africa that the wizard has the power of killing people in this way, probably with the aid of a familiar. <small> &ldquo;DEMONOLOGY&rdquo; <a name="EBDY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDY"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
